[1
Date: Thu, 2 Apr 1998 10:52:22 -0500 (EST)
From: Edward Ryan <ryane@helix.mgh.harvard.edu>

Based on serotyping of the O antigen, _Vibrio cholerae_ is divided into 139
serotypes. _V. cholerae_ O1 and O139 are the serotypes that cause cholera.
_V. cholerae_ O1 is further subdivided into two biotypes: classical and El
Tor. Both cause cholera. The 5th and 6th pandemics were due to classical
O1. The seventh (current) pandemic is due to El Tor. At present it is a
rare event to recover a classical _V. cholerae_ from an individual with
cholera. Most have El Tor O1 or O139 (which is not biotyped). The two
biotypes have a number of differences. Clinically they both cause cholera.
El Tor strains definitely cause cholera gravis. To say that El Tor strains
due not cause classical cholera is a verbal end-run.
--
Edward T. Ryan, M.D., DTM&H
Division of Infectious Diseases
Massachusetts General Hospital
Gray 5; Fruit Street
